Each  auction is modified to sell an option on that good to the  highest bidding proxy, with an initial exercise price set to the second-highest bid received.12 When an option in which a buyer is interested becomes available for the first time, the proxy determines its bid by computing the buyer"s maximum marginal value for the item, and then submits a bid in this amount.
